<reference id="topic" xml:lang="en-us">
<title><xmlelement>topic</xmlelement></title>
<shortdesc>The <xmlelement>topic</xmlelement> element is the top-level DITA element for a
  single-subject topic or article. <ph product="technicalContent learningTraining">Other top-level DITA elements that
   are more content-specific are <xmlelement>concept</xmlelement>, <xmlelement>task</xmlelement>,
    <xmlelement>reference</xmlelement>, and <xmlelement>glossentry</xmlelement>, all of which are
   specializations of the <xmlelement>topic</xmlelement> element.</ph></shortdesc>
<refbody>
<section id="section-1">      <!--RDA: Removed the following paragraph, per comments 
in the DITA 1.3 Third Draft Review. These attributes are 
already given in the attribute table, with more complete and 
up-to-date definitions in the arch spec.

<p>To support applications that are namespace-aware, DITA DTDs and
Schemas provide the following namespaced declarations for topic, and
for topic-level elements derived from topic: <pre xml:space="preserve">
ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.0" 
xmlns:ditaarch="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" 
</pre> In DTDs, the <q>ditaarch</q> prefix is parameterized to enable
future specialization.</p>--> <!--All DITA elements take the &lt;codeph>xmlns=&quot;&quot;&lt;/codeph> fixed
attribute, which puts them into the null namespace by default.  This attribute
is applied via the %global-atts; group.-->    </section>
